Introduction to Debugging in IDE
Learning Objectives
Know how to debug a Java application
Understand breakpoints
Understand the debugger console
Know how to evaluate code fragments
Task
As an introduction to debugging:

watch the following video: Intro to Debugging video
Answer the following questions:

What is the purpose of a breakpoint?

-Pause: acquiring knowledge about a program during its execution.

Does the line of code on a breakpoint run when you start debugging?

-No

How do we debug the next line of code?

-Step Over: It will run the current line of code, run and stop at the next line of code.

What does the step into command do?

-Step Into will step over the method that is about to be invoked, so the debugger will go 
into that method and continue debugging step-by-step.


What is the difference between evaluate expression and evaluate code fragment?

-Evaluate Expression allowsÂ you to type in values and see the results, in the scope of the stopped line.

-Code Fragment allows you to edit a enclosed node of code